        "text": "Since the double sum converges absolutely, we need not specify the order of summation. See the Note at the end of this chapter. The formula then holds for all Re(s) > 1 by analytic continuation. Note that, by Theorem 6.2 in Chapter 3, log ζ(s) is well defined in the simply connected half-plane Re(s) > 1, since ζ has no zeros there. Finally, it is clear that we have",
